text:
@regrann from @sheforumafrica - it’s been a week of accelerated effort and commitments to end violence against women in all its forms. 
we participated at an interactive session on ending violence against women in elections. kudos to @unwomen @unwomen_africa @unwomennigeria on the launch of the programming guide on ending violence against women in elections (vawe). in pic: our founder @inimfonetuk facilitating the interactive discussion at the launch. 
violence against women in elections is not just a violation of the civic rights of women to vote, be voted for, or participate in the electoral process at various levels, it is a denial of their rights to be part of a free, fair and inclusive democracy. these incidents must be addressed because women’s rights are primarily human rights. -

text:
it takes a certain amount of audacity to accuse someone of being a narcissist or a sociopath. an audacity i clearly have. an audacity that has been backed by research, evidence, first-hand experiences, and multiple professional opinions. but not every mean-spirited jerk is a narcissist or a sociopath.
.
i am in no way, shape, or form attempting to silence those who have been personally victimized by a narcissistic sociopath with this post. if you have been victimized by one, i hope you have the same audacity as me to shout it from the rooftops.
.
this is a message for the general public, for those who are misusing these terms on a daily basis due to a lack of education and understanding.
.
gp: please stop throwing out the word “narcissist” to describe your friend that gets botox. please stop throwing around the word “sociopath” when you get dumped by someone that wasn’t that into you. you are *potentially* mislabeling people in your lives when the words vain, selfish, dismissive or aloof may have been better suited. the terms narcissist and sociopath are much, much bigger than vanity, entitlement, disinterest and abandonment. they are the sum of these things and more.
.
learn what it truly means to be a narcissist and/or a sociopath and then use those words carefully. if you can’t name at least five of the nine dsm criteria for npd, maybe don’t use the word narcissist at all. when you throw these words around haplessly, you normalize a serious personality disorder which indirectly normalizes and trivializes the trauma they cause their victims. 💛🦋

text:
@regrann from @sheforumafrica - it’s been a week of accelerated effort and commitments to end violence against women in all its forms. 
we participated at an interactive session on ending violence against women in elections. kudos to @unwomen @unwomen_africa @unwomennigeria on the launch of the programming guide on ending violence against women in elections (vawe). in pic: nigeria country rep. un women, ms. comfort lamptey with our founder @inimfonetuk (r) and our head of contacts mrs. tochi aguiyi-akujua @lynongod at the launch. 
violence against women in elections is not just a violation of the civic rights of women to vote, be voted for, or participate in the electoral process at various levels, it is a denial of their rights to be part of a free, fair and inclusive democracy. these incidents must be addressed because women’s rights are primarily human rights. -

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text: five former nfl cheerleaders are suing the houston texans saying that they would like full compensation for a hostile work environment. the women accused the franchise of paying them less than $7.25 an hour (equal to less than minimum wage in some states), being harrassed, not paying them for public appearances or other tasks like signings, and threatening to fire them for voicing their complaints and having opposing opinions. in wake of the #metoo movement, it’s easy to think that the fight for women’s rights is being resolved. this case shows that women in the workplace (large and small industries) continue to fight for equal rights and pay. this story especially shows how women are seen in male dominated areas, such as the sports industry, and how they are not seen as women who are allowed to speak up and say when they are being mistreated. #ecstorytellers

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
we have all hit rock bottom at some point. the most difficult part of hitting rock bottom, is asking for help. if you’re like me, i tend to hold things in and keep quiet. i don’t usually ask for help because i feel that my problems should be solved by me. it wasn’t until one day, i spoke up. to be honest, it was so hard to. the words didn’t even want to come out of my mouth. i’m glad i did. i was not only at rock bottoms doorsteps, but i was at a point of life or death. i spoke up to save myself. once i did, it’s as if a boulder was taken off of my back. 
have you ever hit rock bottom? comment below and tag someone and let them know that you’re there for them. .
.

text:
tw: sexual violence. @emiliekrajcik shares her experiences with sexual violence and the impact it has had on her life.💜 part 1.
“three years ago, i was sexually assaulted by someone i knew. at time, i did not recognize this as assault. regardless of my conscious awareness of what happened, it shook me to the core. i felt very confused and disoriented about this experience. i had told a friend about the encounter immediately after it happened. several months later after doing research on the topic of assault i confided in her that i felt it was assault or even rape. so i “changed my story” so to speak. she saved all of our messages and began showing them to people including the perpetrator. saying i am a “delusional little girl who just got rejected.”
this was my friend of ten years, who knew all of my friends, family, lived down the road and worked with me every day at the same restaurant. she mentioned this incident to our group of friend, acquaintances, co-workers and even my boss. so this caused me the loss of my social circle, indirectly cost me my job because i was not comfortable working there anymore, and also tension at home because it was a strain on my whole family. that is a severe consequence for simply telling the truth and not only that, it is absolutely unnecessary.
i paid off all my debts and moved from barrie to toronto in search for a safe place to be, and a fresh start. i began searching for creative outlets and found photography. shortly after i moved, the “me too” movement began. with all these stories and information available to me, i realized that what happened to me was extremely wrong and that i am not alone. i thought going through it that i was the only one and nobody would ever be able to understand. i was wrong.
i spent all my time and money doing research and developing my craft as a photographer so i could find a way to express what happened. i thought that if i shared my story it could help someone.“ (to be continued) #ourwomensvoices

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

name: Our Women's Voices
pre_proc_tweet:
on sexual violence pa 2. “that incident changed the course of my life. i will never be the same. though i do not re-live the pain every day, it does still affect me. i have not been able to be sexually active since then because i am so afraid. i find it hard to trust and i am triggered by the news when events such as the kavanaugh trial are occurring.
despite the difficulties, i am stronger now. i have new standards, boundaries and a higher purpose in life. i do not take for granted my health and happiness and i am better for it. i believe this was a pa of my spiritual journey and that i am here to help other women through their experience. i am working towards creating a membership program which will facilitate female friendships, educate women on their rights, advocate for them, and provide them with counselling. i really would like to provide both traditional and non-traditional approaches to healing”  
emilie will speaking at our next workshop on sexual violence and healing, visit the link our bio to rsvp.💜

text:
need to share this today. those from nz know about the story of grace who was allegedly murdered recently while back packing through our beautiful country. this article is so on point i want to print it out and make a wall paper of it.

https://thespinoff.co.nz/society/10-12-2018/rules-wont-save-women/. what will you be teaching your boys? i'm so glad i have a little boy who will be raised with the same standards as his older sister. growing up in a patriarchal community with different rules for boys and girls and constantly hearing that it's ok because he is a boy i am extremely aware of the need to not discriminate based on gender. every where i turned i was told not to do something or dress a particular way because the boys..it was also my fault when we were groped or assaulted. so teach our boys right. grow strong kind men. avoid comparison. do not make sexist jokes in front of your kids. and for goodness sake never say to your boy " why are you behaving like a girl?" as if it were the worst thing on earth.

text: it was important for me to be part of this documentary in sharing my story because i represented, in some way, filipino women, who have faced sexual assault/violence. the filipina speak out campaign i’ve initiated is to bring to light to these issues and hopefully mobilize others to speak out and empower themselves to do what is right. i’m used to doing the interviews but this morning, i was on the hot seat. though for the most part i’ve healed, it was still difficult to talk about it. i am grateful to these women in my life producer shelley jarrett and director beverly vergel accountfull including her team levi de guzman-dj. of course to andrew pasieka and goody cambay. thank you for the opportunity to share my story. i hope you guys can watch the documentary when it screens next year! #whataboutus #documentary #filipinasspeakout #documentary #whataboutus #toronto #torontofilms #interview #metoo #toronto #doc #tv #rachellecruz #behindthescenes #shootlife #documentaryfilm #w’atabwtus

text: a year ago, i posted about this young lady #cyntoiabrown who was pushed on a path of destruction. from her parents,  to the man who pushed her into a slave sex trade as a minor, to the man she was "sold" to, to the court system that gave her a life sentence. and then today, the #tennessee #supremecourt failed her again. they gave her a remaining 51 years. this is ridiculous and frustrating. and where the heck have all the #metoo celebrities and #timesup celebrities that were so vocal just a year ago? marching and speaking about injustice and how they will no longer be silent? and where has the #church been? where has the #christian world been? #god is watching. #freecyntoiabrown

text:
@regran_ed from @sheforumafrica -  it’s been a week of accelerated effort and commitments to end violence against women in all its forms. 
we participated at an interactive session on ending violence against women in elections. kudos to @unwomen @unwomen_africa @unwomennigeria on the launch of the programming guide on ending violence against women in elections (vawe). in pic: nigeria country rep. un women, ms. comfort lamptey with our founder @inimfonetuk (r) and our head of contacts mrs. tochi aguiyi-akujua @lynongod at the launch. 
violence against women in elections is not just a violation of the civic rights of women to vote, be voted for, or participate in the electoral process at various levels, it is a denial of their rights to be part of a free, fair and inclusive democracy. these incidents must be addressed because women’s rights are primarily human rights. -

text:
sadness used to be paralyzing, shameful, and debilitating. but now sadness is just a feeling... it is not who i am.
i feel excited. (i am whole.)
i feel nervous. (i am whole.)
i feel happy. (i am whole.)
i feel sad. (i am whole.) when we ask, "how are you?" notice that the question is not who are you? you are not defined by your feelings. you are whole even if you want to cry your eyes out.

moving louder means moving with these feelings, not against them. we dare you to name your feelings while knowing your wholeness.

text:
hard times are often blessings in disguise. let go and let life strengthen you. no matter how much it hurts, hold your head up high and keep going. this is an important lesson to remember when you’re having a rough day, a bad month, or a crappy year. truth be told, sometimes the hardest lessons to learn are the ones your spirit needs most. your past was never a mistake if you learned from it. 
and remember; 
you’ll never change your life until you change something you do daily. the secret of your success is found in your daily routine. 
be the person your teenage self needed, live the life you always dream of having and be better than yesterday.

text:
all i've ever wanted was to 'make it in new york.' i oft need reminding how hard i've worked to get where i am today & to celebrate every step of my journey.

i've had a grand series of success leading volunteer events, strut out on one date after another in killer heels, even after cutting my feet on glass from a self-made travel gallery wall, loved & lost beloved, survive #metoo every damn day, struggle to make that paper for the liberal arts degree loans and upgrade from queens to ues lifestyle, all the while keeping my smile intact.

it hasn't been easy. at tough times, the point of feeling like giving up, i think of my heroine scarlett o'hara as portrayed by vivien leigh. i recently made my first trip out west in cali to see her star... (swipe👈) if scarlett could come out on top as a savy business woman before her time, in a war torn country, with the love of her life and a killer wardrobe, so can i. after all, she'd say, "tomorrow is another day." i've never been more happy about my achievements and perseverance  than in this moment.

#killingit #workhardplayhard #humblebrag #dogood #itstheclimb #momentforlife #gonewiththewind #scarlettohara #iloveny #dontgiveup #hustle #respecttheprocess #thankyounext #thirtyflirtyandthriving #keepsmiling #dontworrybehappy

text:
어떤 범죄의 피의자와 피해자가 있다.
마땅히 정의로운 사회라면
당연히 피해자 곁에 서줘야한다.
물론 피해자 개 중에는 이득을 얻기위해
거짓을 말하는 자가 100명중 1명 남짓으로 있다.
그렇다고 해서 범죄 자체를 부정할 수 있는가?
피해자를 일단 의심부터 해야하는가?
-
성폭행무고죄로 고통을 겪는 자와
성폭행 피해자 중 누가 수적으로 압도적인가?
그것은 무엇을 의미하는가?
그렇다면 우리가 먼저 고쳐야할 현상은 무엇인가?
이것만 생각해본다면 미투운동기사마다
무고죄 강화부터 주장하고 보는 이들의
뇌주름이 을매나 얕아빠졌는지 알 수 있다.

text: i have been raped twice this year and sexually assault has been going on far too many times around me to count . i try not to speak openly about it because it’s difficult for me to talk about . but i must stress i hate that almost every person ive told has asked why i didnt fight back ! people need to understand how hard it is to act when it’s happening i legit froze up and couldn’t move . i’m now suffering from severe anxiety and ptsd . if you’re a survivor and need help don’t be afraid to ask ! if you need a friend i’m here . and i’ll be blunt i need a friend and i’m reaching out atm ! it’s hard to move on with life it really is . showering or sleeping without feeling like someone might attack you is terrifying . and it’s happened to me in and out of makeup i don’t feel safe in many spaces . all i ask for is respect and support if possible i love u all

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
for my re-write your story tarot challenge, i am using my chakra wisdom oracle cards. . . 
day 9–how did the 3rd event affect how you perceive yourself? completion
🗽
my department chair threatened me in my office in front of students simply because i had sent him an email asking why he had suddenly capitulated to a student after a month of telling me to stand my ground. i had just been ambushed by the student as i was getting off the elevator. i had students with me and students waiting for me in the department office to meet with me during office hours. i asked our administrative assistant if the chair was available but he had someone in his office. i had been dealing with the student all semester and had followed the chair’s instructions.
📚
the week prior, i had met with the chair to review my reappointment paperwork and we discussed the fact that he didn’t have my back, that he routinely capitulated. he didn’t (or wouldn’t) “understand” or acknowledge the situations i addressed. so in the email, i mentioned that this was an example of him not having my back. there was nothing threatening in the email; it was very professional and simply questioned why, after more than a month, he suddenly gave in to the student. he stormed into my office, screamed at me, lunged over my desk at me, stuck his finger in my face, and shouted obscenities. all in front of students. female students. and i calmly sat in my chair and told him to take his finger out of my face. he screamed that he could put his finger anywhere he wanted. so i picked up my phone and called campus police. my students insisted on accompanying me to the police office because they were afraid for me and because they wanted to provide witness statements.
📞
(continued in comments)

the week prior, i had met with the chair to review my reappointment paperwork and we discussed the fact that he didn’t have my back, that he routinely capitulated. he didn’t (or wouldn’t) “understand” or acknowledge the situations i addressed. so in the email, i mentioned that this was an example of him not having my back. there was nothing threatening in the email; it was very professional and simply questioned why, after more than a month, he suddenly gave in to the student. he stormed into my office, screamed at me, lunged over my desk at me, stuck his finger in my face, and shouted obscenities. all in front of students. female students. and i calmly sat in my chair and told him to take his finger out of my face. he screamed that he could put his finger anywhere he wanted. so i picked up my phone and called campus police. my students insisted on accompanying me to the police office because they were afraid for me and because they wanted to provide witness statements.
📞

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green, author
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

regrann from @profirearm  the atf is flawed. bump stocks are out of their power, they stated this in 2010-11 but since the shooter in nevada used one, bump stocks have to be bad.=/ by saying that the atf should not have power over bump stocks and other accessories you grant the atf the power to rule over them.
 the atf outlaws bump stocks by defining them as machine guns even though you have to repeatedly press the trigger to shoot, the bump stock simply allows you to harness the recoil by pulling on the forgrip and pushing your trigger hand while resting your finger on the trigger.
"[a]ny weapon which shoots, is designed to shoot, or can be readily restored to shoot, automatically more than one shot, without manually reloading, by a single function of the trigger." -machine guns legal definition  outlawing a product that we have payed taxes for is either impossible or illegal, it goes against the 5th amendment.
the 5th amendments states that the government can't take your life, property, nor freedom without due process and a grand jury.
"unless on a presentment or indictment of a grand jury"-
"nor be deprived of life, liberty, or property, without due process of law; nor shall private property be taken for public use, without just compensation"  both the atf and government have to much power over the people and what we can own.

text:
“here in the united states, there is a reported rape every 6.2 minutes, and one in five women will be raped in her lifetime... we have an abundance of rape and violence against women in this country and on this earth, though it is almost never a civil rights issue, or a crisis, or even a pattern. violence doesn’t have a race, a class, a religion, or nationality, but it does have a gender. (it doesn’t mean all men are violent, most are not. men obviously also suffer violence, largely at the hands of other men, and every violent death, every assault is terrible). it’s a system of control. it’s why so many intimate-partner murders are of women who dared to break up with those partners. as a result, it imprisons a lot of women. 
a woman is beaten every nine seconds in this country. just to be clear: not nine minutes, but nine seconds. it’s the number one cause of injury to american women; of the two million injured annually, more than half a million of those injuries require medical attention while about 145,000 require overnight hospitalization, according to the centers for disease control, and you don’t want to know about the dentistry needed afterwards. spouses are the leading cause of death for pregnant women in the united states... this is everyone’s problem. it’s not isolated. it has to change.”— solnit, “men explain things to me”. #endviolence #smashpatriarchy #civilrights #humanrights  #everyonesproblem #normalizevulnerability #endgenderroles #teachcompassion #wewillnotbesilenced #metoo

text:
one of the ongoing projects of #feminist #activism has been to bridge the public-private divide through which #women are confined to the 'private' realm -- such as homes, where their #labour is both used as the foundation of daily life, and devalued as not being 'real #work' and hence not deserving of pay. further, women are told that the '#privatespace' is the 'appropriate' #space for them, and the logic of '#safety' is used to justify this. 
in this poem yukta relates the experience of being a woman walking down the streets of #kathmandu and claiming that space. over the course of the poem she goes from wanting to be invisible, to wanting to be invincible. 
@yukta.bajracharya is a part of @wordwarriorsnepal, a kathmandu-based group of young #poets leading the #spokenword movement in #nepal. they aim to use spoken word as 'a regenerative and empowering tool to bring out stories and issues of the #nepali people, and utilize its potential to initiate #dialogue for social change'

listen to her poem here, and then come over to our stories to join the conversation this week. we are talking about public spaces, who gets to own them and the consequences that come with it.

text:
⛄❄проснувшись рано утром 1-го января, все детки спросонья бегут к ёлочке🌲, потому что под ней для них дедушка мороз оставил долгожданные подарки🎅! и как же удивится ваш ребёнок, увидев не просто коробку или пакет, а  волшебно упакованный подарок🎁! такую коробочку малыш(ка) не станет сразу разрывать, чтобы добраться до содержимого☝! вы можете вместе рассматривать коробочку😍 и заодно поиграть в игру "как думаешь, что там?"🤔...
.
 подборка оригинальных идей для упаковки новогодних подарков в карусели, листайте👉:
🔷эффектные прорези. особенно ярко смотрится когда коробка и упаковочная бумага контрастируют🤗
🔷 коробочка-машинка для любимых мальчишек. просто приклейте колёса от сломанной машинки к коробке и готово🚗
🔷самодельные варежки смотрятся очень мило и необычно😻
🔷декор из леденцов-двойной подарок для сладкоежек🍭
🔷коробка-мордочка оленя,  смотрится очень по-новогоднему🌲
🔷циферблат новогодних часов-заветные минуты для желаний🕚
🔷наклейте на коробку  фото того, кому этот подарок предназначен! вот все удивятся, увидев себя на коробочке!🤗
.
с детками постарше можно изготавливать праздничную упаковку вместе😉! весело и полезно проведёте время с ребёнком😊👍!
.
не жалейте ваши ❤❤, чтобы мы не пропадали из ленты!
.
#splushka_friend_newyear #сплюшка #сплюшкасаратов #игрушкисаратов  #игрушки #metoo #новыйгод #подарок #готовимсякновомугоду  #праздниккнамприходит #мама #вселучшеедетям

text: (trigger warning) how truly beautiful it is when we are able to see our most painful experiences in a new light... whereas i once was ashamed for having stayed in an abusive relationship and for being a victim of sexual assault, i now see my past as a means by which i am learning to set healthy boundaries, discovering my limitless resilience, and developing a deep sense of self love and respect. i want to talk openly about these traumas in the hopes of letting other survivors know that you are not alone, that you do not have to struggle in silence, and that there is hope of healing. normalcy and stability will come again and while you won’t be able to return to the same person you were, it’s because you will emerge a stronger, more enlightened, more radiant version of the you that you were always meant to be. through the darkness, you will shine ✨ #metoo #survivor #healing #youarenotalone #shameresilience #souljourney #selflove #safespace #psychopathfree #sunset #inspired

text:
strength: the quality or state of being strong; a good or beneficial quality of a person or thing.
*
* 
what strength is to me might look different than anothers. most people would not know i have been clean/sober going on six years now. that i can say "me too" with my head held high, or that at 24 years young my mother passed suddenly and i now provide for my 15 year old brother.
*
these events i have lived through! * 
we all have a story, a story we have lived through to see the next day! life its self can be cruel and deceitful. let us remember we do not have to act out the same; we can live through life with kindness, joy, and strength! * 
stand proud for yourself! your strength is unique to your person. surround yourself with others of strength and share your experiences.

text:
dipa karmakar is only the 5th women to have successfully developed the produnova, one of the most difficult vaults competed in women's gymnastics. 
born in a remote part of india and with flat feet, not many would have given her a chance to achieve what she did. 
dipa karmakar has truly nailed the fact that indian women can make anything happen with their dedication & courage. gymnastics, not so popular sport in india, took a turn for better when dipa karmakar etched india's name on the map of the world gymnastics after qualifying for the finals in rio. 
she is now, recipient of padma shri, rajiv gandhi khel ratna and arjuna awards.

sanfe salutes dipa karmakar's spirit to inspire young gymnasts to work and bring laurels to the nation. 
#standupforyourself

tweet_full:
dipa karmakar is only the 5th women to have successfully developed the produnova, one of the most difficult vaults competed in women's gymnastics. 
born in a remote part of india and with flat feet, not many would have given her a chance to achieve what she did. 
dipa karmakar has truly nailed the fact that indian women can make anything happen with their dedication & courage. gymnastics, not so popular sport in india, took a turn for better when dipa karmakar etched india's name on the map of the world gymnastics after qualifying for the finals in rio. 
she is now, recipient of padma shri, rajiv gandhi khel ratna and arjuna awards.

sanfe salutes dipa karmakar's spirit to inspire young gymnasts to work and bring laurels to the nation.

because we have accepted to hide the abuse we suffer, because we have decided to be silent through the hurt. because we don’t speak loud enough or often enough. because of the fear, the tears and the stares. but no more! 
it is time to hear me too, it is our time to stand up and fight against any abuse or violation of any girl, woman or child. we will no longer sit still and be silent. 
we will honour ourselves by standing up and speaking as we take back our power.

the time is now. it is time for change!
.

text:
the #metoo movement, which was sparked last fall after the new york times and the new yorker brought to light harvey weinstein’s long history of sexual harassment and assault. shortly thereafter, women across the world shared their own experiences — demonstrating, in the process, just how many have kept quiet for years about discrimination, abuse, and rape. powerful men in media and politics have been forced to resign as a result, after allegations surfaced about their behavior.

but rather than encouraging employees to speak up about harassment, or implementing better training programs, many wall street executives have had a different reaction to the #metoo movement. according to a report this week from @bloomberg, male executives are❗️avoiding one-on-one dinners with women and refusing to sit next to them on flights, out of fear of being falsely accused of doing or saying something inappropriate ❗️ this type of backlash, of course, threatens to do real harm to the careers of women in banking, where success depends in large part on networking and going out to dinner — oftentimes with just men. “women are grasping for ideas on how to deal with it because it’s affecting our careers,” karen elinski, the president of the financial women’s association.⠀
⠀
"instead of going out of their way to avoid being alone with female colleagues, male executives can simply try behaving themselves", an unnamed investment adviser told bloomberg. his advice to executives who worry that their actions might be misinterpreted: “just don’t be an asshole.” word.⠀
________⠀

text:
over the weekend hlokomela & 225 of hoedspruit’s farm workers march in solidarity with the “16 days of activism against women and children abuse”. this march forms part of our annual “#aids day” celebrations, & this year the event was hosted at rederberg estate.  the 3km walk started at the snake park road & ended at the rederberg soccer field towards moriah. the event’s aim was to raise awareness on hiv & aids, remember the loved ones we’ve lost to the disease, & to sensitise community members about gender based violence.

as part of the day’s activities , two local female soccer clubs participated in a friendly soccer match, with the winning team walking away with a full new soccer kit. (including kit, flags and soccer nets.) other activities included a dialogue on the theme “shatter the silence. stop the violence. #metoo”, a talk by guest speaker, captain thete,  from the saps on gender based violence, & a candle light memorial to remember & honour those who have passed over the last 13 years.

a big thank you to our partners for delivering the services that made this day possible. thank you to the caterers, entertainment team & the nompilos for making this such a fun day. 
a big thank you in particular to the rederberg estates, saps hoedspruit, maruleng traffic department, department of social development & @discovery_sa for their massive support.

text:
womens circle ⭕️ on friday we were lucky enough to host this amazing group of women for a podcast.
we gathered, we grazed on black bean brownies, we giggled at ridiculous cutesy terminology for ‘lady bits’ and we gave thought to the topics of patriarchy, the #metoo movement, the #stopkavanaugh story and what it is to be a woman in ireland today.

thank you so much @wildflower.adventures @universaltao.ie @suitsedit and aoife martin for sharing your experiences, your wisdom and your time. 
keep your eyes peeled for when this one goes live : it’s a goody 🙌🏻 #patriarchy #women #ireland #transrightsarehumanrights #inclusion #diversity #sexeducation #taoism #jadeegg #greatminds #wanderingintowellness #podcast #happiness #healthandwellness #consent

text:
a piece by @mwolfpoetry, called “stanger”, about sexual assaults and harassment.
.
this is what she said in her caption:
.
“we all know what went down with kavanaugh and christine ford. time and time again, victims of sexual assault won’t come out and share their story because they’re afraid of being targeted and deemed liars.
.
this is what happened a few days ago. i won’t get into details because any news outlet can tell you exactly how it all happened. what i will say is: i believe you. i believe your story. i believe your pain and i will always be vocal about this. #ibelieveher”
.
#nomeansno #harassment #metoo #metoomovement

text:
вчера "какой то тип гражданской наружности" нашей "маме" ц̶в̶е̶т̶ы̶ ̶п̶о̶д̶а̶р̶и̶л̶ и пуле пытался знаки внимания оказывать.
'
и если успех возлюбленнойда у представителей противоположного пола вполне объясним, то пуле, так на секундочку, через 2 недели стукнет только 11 лет. 😲
'
впрочем, с извращугами скоро будет покончено к̶о̶с̶т̶р̶ы̶ ̶и̶н̶к̶в̶и̶з̶и̶ц̶и̶и̶ ̶у̶ж̶е̶ ̶р̶а̶з̶г̶о̶р̶а̶ю̶т̶с̶я̶, по крайней мере в #internet. к примеру #facebook уже обновил правила публикации спорного контента. например, сообщения срамного содержания будут расцениваться как явное сексуальное домогательство. а фраза "хочу развлечься сегодня вечером", как не явного. 😲
'
напомню что #instagram принадлежит facеbook, таким образом велика вероятность того что и на эту соц. сеть рапространятся те же правила.
'
я конечно понимаю что перед смертью не надышишся, но время пока у вас ещё есть. #ноэтонеточно (;
'

text:
happy monday everyone!! 🌸
with christmas approaching soon it’s important to remember this is a time of giving. just one good deed of the day, as simple as saying hello to someone who looks lonely can make such an impact. just as malala’s quote says one voice can be so powerful in a crowd of silence, especially in support of the injustices in the world. so remember this christmas to love and support those in need of it 💗 •

text:
be careful who you bury. 
it’s all fun and games until well intentioned people unearth them,

shake the barrow dirt from their clothes,

and link hands,

bracing them behind the back of the newly emerged,

placing their bewildered feet on the pathway of life.

be careful who you bury. 
you may discover the prepossessing puppet who bowed to your depraved structure was something else entirely. 
you buried steel beneath that delicate headstone.

darling, this is not your grave.

text:
on human rights day, the world marks 70 years since the adoption of the udhr. the declaration was born out of wwii to ensure that all human beings are born free and equal with dignity and rights (article 1). sadly, we’re not there yet. today, 50% of refugees uprooted from their homes from conflict, persecution or natural disasters are women and girls. and their specific needs and voices are often neglected. 
thankfully, insightful roadmaps are provided. a report, turning promises into action: gender equality in the 2030 agenda for sustainable development, exposes the major gaps in current data about what works for women and girls, particularly those who are most marginalised. so what’s the key takeaway? gender equality, women’s human rights and the intersectional approach woven into the sdgs are critical for achieving every one of the 17 goals. let’s take it from there!

for more, click the link in our bio.

stand up 4 human rights. we see you. she matters.

text:
بـ تعرض للتحرش الجنسي من وانا عندي 5 سنين 
لسه فاكرة لمسة إيده عليا ونظراته
الموضوع كان مريب بدون ما أدخل في تفاصيل كتير
اتعرضت للتحرش الجنسي من خالي.

لباقي القصة: https://www.facebook.com/thebussyproject/posts/2107106959335257?__tn__=k-r 
كتير بـ يحصلنا مواقف من غير موافقتنا في علاقتنا بالآخرين، من أول طريقة سلام مش حابينها حتى لو من حد قريب، لحد الموافقة المفترضة في العلاقات الزوجية.

في إطار حملة الـ 16 يوم لمناهضة العنف ضد المرأة، تقوم خريطة التحرش ومشروع بصى بحملة مشتركة عن الموافقة في العلاقات وأهميتها في تحديد الأفعال التي تعتبر تحرش أو عنف جنسي.
تقوم بصى خلال شهر نوفمبر وديسمبر بنشر قصص من سيدات ورجال عن تجارب تعرضوا لها في علاقاتهم الشخصية مع آخرين بدون موافقتهم.

ابعتولنا قصصكم عن طريق الاستمارة 
https://goo.gl/forms/daazuqogqqgarexg3
لمتابعة الحملة على صفحة خريطة التحرش
facebook.com/harassmapegypt/
harassmap خريطة التحرش الجنسي
#بعد_إذني #بصى #خريطة_التحرش #16_يوم #التحرش_في_الشارع

i’ve been sexually abused since i was 5 years old.
i can still feel his hand on me, his leers.
without going into more details, the whole thing was creepy.
i was molested by my uncle.
for the rest of the story follow the link: https://www.facebook.com/thebussyproject/posts/2107106959335257?__tn__=k-r

from an unwanted handshake or hug—even from the people closest to us—to the so-called “implied consent” in marital sexual intercourse, we’re often put in situations that happen without our consent.

the bussy project and harassmap are launching a joint campaign within the framework of the “16 days of activism to end violence against women” campaign about consent in relationships and its importance in defining what constitutes sexual harassment and sexual violence.
to share your story anonymously, please use this form: https://goo.gl/forms/daazuqogqqgarexg3

to follow the campaign, please check out harassmap’s facebook page: facebook.com/harassmapegypt/
#askfirst #bussy #harassmap #gendertech #16days #metoo #storytelling #endsh #orangetheworld

all hail the king of kings!!! in humble adoration, i return to give you praise. .

believe when i say, god is good, god is real and he is always in a good mood!!! .

i am eternally grateful for the gift of salvation and all that comes with it.
.

lord i return all the glory to you.
.
.

there is nothing i did this year or will still do that was by my strength or doing. it was/is simply by the grace of god.
.
.

i did not qualify but his call qualified me. so if you sometimes feel like you don't qualify, guess what? #metoo. but you need to move beyond that and believe you are worth his investment/calling.
.

if he calls you, then he qualifies you. settle it in your mind. galatians 2:20 will help us all... if he can use me, trust me, he can use you. the question is, "are you avaliable".
.
.

this year is indeed my year of covenant realities.
.

i also want to thank you for being part of my 2018.
.
.

i am grateful and i return to thank him
.
.

text: i still whole heartedly support #metoo despite my experiences  it is already tremendously successful  and i believe its time for all men to support the rise of the divine feminine especially in cultural and governmental affairs. we need more nurturing and thoughtful leadership  in these powerful positions... hollywood is where social justice and other issues travel  so it makes sense that they should lead it  and i applaud the women doing the work. as for me i have been a playboy all my life i accept that the new more accurate term for playboy is womanizer  therefore i accept that i have been part of the problem  and i’m here now to be part of the solution  hollywood is a great place to brand an idea and it has been tremendously helpful in pointing out where we as a society need lots of work  however hollywood is also the place where money and fame are sought after the most ... in every great revolution there is some collateral damage  i am sad  for the many men who are being extorted or unjustly accused (and there are many)  but  it is worth it if my daughters will live in a world where the agenda for women is advanced  i am fearful left that without a shift to balance this current wave of unconscious masculine leadership, we as a species could be fucked... the future must be more brown, (inclusive) ..more conscious ,and more feminine ❤️

for me everyday is human rights day. as a human rights activist for the last 18 years, upholding and fighting for the rights of the marginalised and vulnerable has been my passion. everyday the rights of the less priviledged, marginalised are abused all over the world. we must all play our part in being defenders of human rights and hold those who break them accountable. all rights are equal. human rights are for everyone. everyone should be treated equally. we can create change in our homes, work, faith communities, sports, communities etc. we should all be human rights defenders.

text: @malala has been such a foundational part of the movement towards #gender #equality that to have the opportunity to see her in person tonight brought me to tears. she was passionate, she was inspirational, but most of all she was filled with drive - a moment did not go by that she did not take the chance to use her platform to speak about #refugees, or the 130 million girls who aren’t in school, or the dangers of terrorist organisations destroying childhoods and livelihoods. she spoke of her family - “many girls spoke out, but the difference is my dad didn’t stop me [whilst other girls’ parents did]”. she spoke of the #metoo movement - “it is crucial because it started a conversation in the west on the topic of violence and harassment of women and girls - something we are all too happy to talk about when it happens in pakistan or india, but not in so-called ‘developed’ nations!” and she spoke about changemaking - “i realised that if i do speak out, they might target me. but if i don’t speak out, then we have to live in this situation forever.” but for me, the most pivotal moment came in the realisation that she is still only a young woman starting her journey into adulthood (like myself, and many other young people i know). when @annabelcrabb asked her about the most difficult part of moving out of home, her answer? “laundry.”

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
💙thank you💙
.
.
for the past week we have been raising awareness about the international campaign with the aim of #eliminatingviolenceagainstwomen. today we would like to say thank you for all the enthusiasm we received, regarding this difficult and extremely important topic. .
.
as some of you may know, last tuesday we held a stall in aid of #evaw. a communal 📖 was left, so people could write their own experiences down so they could be shared anonymously.
.
.
we are sharing the stories written in the book with you. please take a minute to read them, be mindful of what sort of negative attitudes they are perpetuating and what we can do to become better as a community.
.
.
sometimes a joke isn’t just a “joke”, it’s the normalisation of an attitude which is toxic. this toxic attitude seeps in further into the mindsets of our society, normalising more violent behaviour such as rape and murder
.
.
we hope that this initiative has sparked a conversation between yourself and those around you. we believe injustice against women needs to be stopped and it starts with us. #thishappenedhere.
.
.

text:
в ответ на нашумевшую кампанию #metoo, когда женщины вспоминали о своих давних моментах насилия и пострадало не мало мужчин, в одной из самых мужских отраслей - в финансовой - на уолл стрит появились негласные правила:
- никаких обедов с женщинами коллегами
- никогда не садиться на соседнее кресло в самолете с женщиной
- букировать гостиничные номера на разных этажах - избегать встреч наедине, особенно в помещениях с закрытыми окнами и дверями
таким образом, у женщин в данной сфере появились дополнительные сложности в построении карьеры. учитывая мужское господство на ключевых должностях уолл стрит, данные правила препятствуют естественному процессу наставничества со стороны мужчин, которые могут помочь им подняться по карьерной лестнице.

text:
hey ladies 👋🏼 so many new faces here that i wanted to (re)introduce myself to y’all.
.
i grew up in the upper midwest and, even though we now call boston home, i brought my accent with me.. someone recently thought i was canadian because of how i pronounced ‘bag’.
.
i’m the oldest kid in my family and have two younger sisters @emmalinestafki @lydiarose180 and a younger brother. most of our grade school education was completed at home, so we learned early on how to be both friends and siblings.
.
my husband collin and i met in college. he was getting his engineering degree from @iowastateu and i was studying business at @uwriverfalls . we’ve been together 10 years, married for almost 4💏
.
🎡i went to london for the first time last year and i’m convinced i need to live there some day!
.
i’ve experienced sexual assault and sexual harassment #metoo . i’ve also witnessed many women i’m close to go through similar struggles #believeher . it took a long time, but i’m at a place where i feel empowered to use my platform to share my story and advocate for those who share this kind of trauma❤️i’m energized to create a better world for women #feminist
.
i’m a #gemini ♊️(love to talk, intellectual, witty, imaginative, fickle/restless), a questioner tendency (always need to know why + be allowed to come to my own conclusions), and an enneagram type 2 (helper).
.
i’d describe myself as an extroverted-introvert. i love being around people and socializing, but it can also feel draining when i over-commit. i need my alone time where i can unwind and recharge🧖‍♀️
.
i’m pretty sensitive (aka can cry just thinking about something sad or especially sweet). sappy commercials usually get me too – if it’s for a @subaru_usa i’m probably going to bawl 😭
.
i love my kitties lola and sebastian, but dogs are pretty cool too 😽
.
tell me about you! where are you from?👇
.

text:
se quest’anno si è parlato tanto del movimento #metoo che ha portato a galla molti scheletri nell’armadio, in #coreadelsud sta ri-emergendo un altro tipo di movimento di cui non si era più parlato da tempo. con lo scandalo della cantante tiffany del gruppo girls generation, il #debttoo ha ripreso a fare vittime, o meglio, a mettere gli #artisti di fronte alle colpe dei propri genitori a causa di debiti o frode. un articolo interessante di seoulbeats (vedi commenti) ci spiega che il #debttoo si è sviluppato in modo abbastanza complesso nel mondo dello showbiz coreano differenziandosi dai casi accaduti in occidente aggiungendo, poi, che la base su cui si fonda tale movimento sarebbe quella del concetto di collettività: l’armonia e l’unità all’interno di un gruppo prevalgono di più rispetto ai desideri e le libertà individuali. a tutto ciò, quindi, bisogna aggiungere l’idea di famiglia e immagine pubblica che si ha in #asia dove la prima è determinata da un forte senso di unità e grande rispetto verso i genitori mentre la seconda con una percezione perfetta del singolo individuo all’interno della società. 
senza dilungarci troppo e ritornando al caso tiffany, la cantante ha dovuto affrontare le conseguenze di un caso di truffa e frode che suo padre ha causato ai danni di un conoscente. la vittima ha raccontato la sua storia attraverso un post che ha fatto circolare in rete spiegando che dopo aver dato i soldi al padre di tiffany, quest’ultimo sia poi sparito senza la possibilità di contattarlo e riavere indietro i soldi. dopo l’uscita della notizia, la cantante ha rilasciato una dichiarazione nella quale spiega come lei stessa in passato abbia sempre sofferto per le azioni fraudolente del padre tanto da porre fine a qualsiasi rapporto familiare. infine, ha chiesto scusa alla vittima per le azioni di suo padre. 
che cosa ne pensate? tante sono le differenze sia culturali sia di pensiero o principi tra occidente e oriente ma noi di asianotebook abbiamo sempre pensato che in entrambe non si riesca mai ad arrivare a un punto intermedio perchè si passa sempre da un eccesso all’altro creando, a volte, delle situazioni surreali.

text:
svenska kyrkans julkampanj för det internationella arbetet har i år temat en flicka är född. här läggs fokus på hur olika villkor det är för de flickor som föds till världen. genom olika projekt vill svenska kyrkan i samverkan med andra arbeta långsiktigt, rättighetsbaserat och genom teologisk reflektion för att förändra förutsättningarna i världen.
det är inget nytt att flickor är särskilt utsatta. i veckan kommer vi att fira lucia, en kvinna på sicilien som kämpade för rätten att bestämma över sin tro, sin kropp och sitt liv. på nobeldagen delas fredspriset ut till två personer, som aktivt arbetar mot sexuellt våld i krigssituationer.
inte heller behöver vi åka långt bort. mäns våld mot kvinnor är en stor riskfaktor också i sverige. det vet vi både från #metoo och kyrkans motsvarighet #vardeljus. men nu lyfter vi upp allt i ljuset med hopp om förändring.
därför bjuder svenska kyrkan helsingborg under december in alla som vill att delta i kampanjen thursdays in black. den som vill klär sig i svart, kanske med en knapp eller en selfie med hashtaggen #thursdaysinblack, för att öka medvetenheten och bjuda in till samtal, om hur vi tillsammans kan skapa en tryggare värld, utan våld, för alla.

👂
👂
ive had thousands of conversations with men and women and not once have i heard a man say “it's not what you say, but how you say it”, this phrase is exclusive to women.

👂
👂

text:
this picture was taken tonight at 6:47pm, a picture of me smiling..... with teeth showing! i must have been feeling great. i never smile with my teeth..... i felt beautiful, gorgeous, understood, and respected. at 6:55 i hung up a call with a close friend to go through the tsa security line at san diego international airport. @tsa this is when you brought me down. took my self worth. took it all, molested me, violated me. you basically threw it in the trash. i was essentially detained for being transgender..... at san diego international airport my groin was flagged on the body scan. and i refused to be searched and have my groin patted down by a @tsa officer, who refused to call me a woman, the entire time. i was misgendered and treated more poorly than i ever have been since going through transition.  i was told i have two options. allow them to rescan me and program the machine to scan me as a man, or be arrested if i was patted down in the groin area and anything was felt between my legs. 
it’s interesting how your subordinates supported me, told me that they didn’t understand why this was happening. told me that they were sorry that this was happening. grabbing handfuls of paper towels for me to dry my tears and wick away the snot that was dripping down my face as i cried and shook uncontrollably with terror. 
i took my only option to make it home. i took away everything i’ve worked for and stood up for when i cowardly gave up my fight and allowed you to scan me as a male, only to have my chest flagged on the body scanner. only to be molested on my chest. simply to end the tirade. so i could go home. i gave myself up to you. 
i didn’t survive 7+ years of childhood sexual trauma to go through this as an adult. i didn’t stand up to the last man who violated me to be molested by a “public servant”.
i will stand up. and i will fight. because no man, woman, or child ever deserves to be treated the way i was at sdia, or anywhere else in america. what lies between my legs is my business.
#metoo 
i am so depressed i can’t stop crying. i was told that because of the way i present myself, that this was my fault. this isn’t how i present myself. this is me.

text:
#triggerwarning #mynewnormal #mynewreality 
last week i fell prey to an individual that allowed his demons to take control of him and work their evil on me.  i was shopping, i had put my items in the back of my car and then went to out my cart away as i always do...my car doors still unlocked.  30 seconds, that is all it took, and he managed to sneak into the backseat of my car without me seeing him.  please, please, please be careful, be vigilant, be aware...and always always lock your doors even if just returning your cart to the cart return.

my attacker has since been found...but he took his own life in the process.  it is an odd hallow feeling...but i am thankful he can no longer hurt anyone else.  and, he will not destroy me nor my spirit...i refuse to give him that power after all he tried to take from me.  i survived, i am alive, and i will rise!
.
.
.
.
#becareful #stayvigilant #stayaware #survivor #iamasurvivor #rapesurvivor #metoo

text:
i realize that i'm never going to fit in anyone's box. like lots of little black girls, i was taught that my personality, excitement and curiosity was a nuisance and i needed to go sit down and stop being "fast". this rejection taught me to very powerful lessons. 1) i had to work hard as fuck to be loved and if it didn't work, it was my fault. 2) i would never be good enough to be loved just for being me. i don’t even need to tell you the type of pain that incision in my life from learning these lessons.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it has taken and continues to take work at accepting all this glorious, juicy, brilliant divineness. but this is the healing work. regardless of what anyone else did to me, it's my responsibility to heal the broken places because that little girl is still deserving of love and acceptance.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
she deserves to be seen and i'll be gotdam if i'm going to stand in the way of her getting her shine!⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
if you're ready to give that lil girl in you everything she deserves, click the link in my bio and pick up my ultimate healing tool kit. she deserves it.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#healblackwomen #fuckthatcape #protectblackgirls

text:
my desk is brimming with activity, tasks that need completed, and moments to sip early grey tea. i awoke to a start this morning with great positive thoughts for this monday and week. my feelings have not changed god gave me another day on this earth to give of myself to others. as i sit and reflect this morning, my mind wanders from the holiday activities planned, to finish decorating for christmas, to baking with my teens and husband, to wait when did i go back to the abused child of my past and tears. the television is on id channel and they are talking of a little girl who was sexually abused. i am there again crying for myself and that little girl that no one helped. i am mad at myself for going down the rabbit hole this morning.  my mind wanders over the lifetime of abuse i suffered until i said, "no more!" then, i find my strength and pull from within, it will not win, i am going to love, show this world compassion, center myself in peace, and focus on my angel that hangs over my desk. a gift from an artist friend and i center in light...

.

text:
the me too movement (or #metoo movement), with many local and international alternative names, is a movement against sexual harassment and sexual assault  #metoo spread virally in october 2017 as a hashtag on social media in an attempt to demonstrate the widespread prevalence of sexual assault and harassment, especially in the workplaceit followed soon after the sexual abuse allegations against harvey weinstein. tarana burke, an american social activist and community organizer, began using the phrase "me too" as early as 2006, and the phrase was later popularized by american actress alyssa milano, on twitter in 2017. milano encouraged victims of sexual harassment to tweet about it and "give people a sense of the magnitude of the problem"⠀
⠀
